Usually, what game
developers end up doing is

00:15:35.560 --> 00:15:37.870
they do a small launch in
maybe a certain smaller

00:15:37.870 --> 00:15:39.780
country like, let's say, Canada.

00:15:39.780 --> 00:15:41.860
Or, they might spend a
bunch of money up-front

00:15:41.860 --> 00:15:44.090
on trying to do some
paid user acquisition.

00:15:44.090 --> 00:15:45.800
But in this case,
ZenStudios didn't

00:15:45.800 --> 00:15:47.950
need to do either
