talk about staged rollouts.

00:16:04.400 --> 00:16:06.950
This feature is all about
keeping the momentum

00:16:06.950 --> 00:16:09.570
going when you push out
new versions of your app.

00:16:09.570 --> 00:16:12.310
When we talked with Jack
Threads, they said-- hey,

00:16:12.310 --> 00:16:14.230
we want to redo our
Android app and make it

00:16:14.230 --> 00:16:16.097
the best mobile experience ever.

00:16:16.097 --> 00:16:18.180
But if you're going to
take on a project this big,

00:16:18.180 --> 00:16:19.270
you're going to
be really worried.

00:16:19.270 --> 00:16:20.728
If you have an
eCommerce app, you'd

00:16:20.728 --> 00:16:22.670
be afraid to touch
the checkout flow

00:16:22.670 --> 00:16:25.237
because you might
break everything.

00:16:25.237 --> 00:16:27.320
Can you imagine having an
eCommerce app and no one

00:16:27.320 --> 00:16:29.240
could buy anything
for a few days?

00:16:29.240 --> 00:16:31.080
That would be a huge problem.

00:16:31.080 --> 00:16:33.790
So what they said was
with staged rollouts,

00:16:33.790 --> 00:16:36.360
they were willing to touch
these trickier bits of code

00:16:36.360 --> 00:16:39.290
and make such a fundamental
change without all

00:16:39.290 --> 00:16:40.984
this worry about breaking stuff.

00:16:40.984 --> 00:16:42.900
And they said that they
can now move much more

00:16:42.900 --> 00:16:45.412
quickly with their small team.

00:16:45.412 --> 00:16:47.120
During the rollouts,
what they do is they

00:16:47.120 --> 00:16:50.657
check the desired metrics,
the stats, the ratings,

00:16:50.657 --> 00:16:52.490
the installs, and the
crashes, and make sure

00:16:52.490 --> 00:16:54.480
that this new version is
performing at least as

00:16:54.480 --> 00:16:55.920
well as the previous one.

00:16:55.920 --> 00:16:58.250
So as a result, they
now use staged rollouts

00:16:58.250 --> 00:17:00.160
with every single
launch they do.

00:17:00.160 --> 00:17:02.500
And most importantly,
because Google Play

00:17:02.500 --> 00:17:04.554
is such a great platform
for trying new stuff,

00:17:04.554 --> 00:17:06.970
they actually try out their
new features on Android first.

